<subSubSection pageId="20" pageNumber="36" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="20.[136,1452,662,895]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">
Description. See 
<bibRefCitation author="Wang" box="[371,570,662,687]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" pagination="231 - 244" refId="ref18383" refString="Wang, L. Y., Li, Z. X., Zhou, K. X., Zhang, Z. S. 2015. Redescription of three Hippasa species from China (Araneae: Lycosidae), with a proposed species group-division and diagnosis. Zootaxa, 3974 (2): 231 - 244. doi: 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3974.2.7." type="journal article" year="2015">
Wang 
<emphasis box="[439,486,663,687]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2015)
</bibRefCitation>
for both sexes. Habitus, male palp and epigyne as in 
<figureCitation box="[1135,1269,663,687]" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="18.[155,218,1979,2001]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,672,1935]" captionTargetId="figure-182@18.[189,1398,672,1936]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figure 23. Hippasa holmerae Thorell, 1895, male and female from Hainan. A. Male habitus, dorsal view; B. Female habitus, dorsal view; C. Left male palp, bulbus, ventral view; D. Same, retrolateral view; E. Left male palp, ventral view; F. Same, retrolateral view; G. Epigyne, ventral view; H. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars: A–B=1.0mm; C–H=0.2mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5366362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5366362/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">Figs 23A–H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1279,1355,663,687]" captionStart="Figure 24" captionStartId="19.[155,218,2007,2029]" captionText="Figure 24. Hippasa holmerae Thorell, 1895, male from Hainan. A. Left male palp, bulbus, ventral view; B. Same, retrolateral view; C. terminal apophysis, ventral view; D. Embolus and terminal apophysis,ventralview;E.Embolus, ventral view; F.Median apophysis, ventral view. Scale bars: A–B=0.1mm; C=0.03mm; D, F=0.04mm; E=0.02mm." pageId="20" pageNumber="36">24A–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1366,1448,662,686]" captionStart="Figure 25" captionStartId="20.[155,218,2016,2038]" captionText="Figure 25. Hippasa holmerae Thorell, 1895, male and female from Hainan. A. Left male palp, ventral view; B. Same, retrolateral view; C. Epigyne, ventral view; D. Vulva, dorsal view. Scale bars=0.2mm." pageId="20" pageNumber="36">25A–D</figureCitation>
. Material examined. 
<specimenCount box="[405,438,697,721]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" type="male">1♂</specimenCount>
(
<typeStatus box="[453,548,697,721]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barrion, Barrion-Dupo &amp; Heong" authorityYear="2012" box="[584,731,697,721]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hippasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinsiloides">
<emphasis box="[584,731,697,721]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">H. sinsiloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<specimenCount box="[746,779,697,721]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" type="female">5♀</specimenCount>
(
<typeStatus box="[794,898,697,721]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barrion, Barrion-Dupo &amp; Heong" authorityYear="2012" box="[935,1081,697,721]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hippasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinsiloides">
<emphasis box="[935,1081,697,721]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">H. sinsiloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Panja Town, Songtao Reservoir, 
<date box="[136,246,732,756]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" value="2011-04-03">3.IV.2011</date>
, A.T. Barrion, J.L.A. Catindig &amp; S.C. Villareal leg. (HANU); 
<specimenCount box="[917,952,732,756]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" type="male">1♂</specimenCount>
<specimenCount box="[952,985,732,756]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" type="female">2♀</specimenCount>
, Ding’an County, Huangzhu, 
<date box="[1305,1447,732,756]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" value="2007-08-21">21.VIII.2007</date>
, F. Zhang &amp; G.X. Han leg. (SWUC). Distribution. 
<collectingCountry box="[331,395,801,825]" name="China" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[409,482,801,825]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">Fujian</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[492,619,801,825]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[630,725,801,825]" country="China" name="Guangxi" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">Guangxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[735,815,801,825]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">Hainan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[825,899,802,825]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">Hunan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[910,990,801,825]" country="China" name="Jiangxi" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">Jiangxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1000,1081,801,825]" name="Taiwan" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, Yunnan), 
<collectingCountry box="[1194,1251,801,825]" name="India" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">India</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1262,1386,801,825]" name="Philippines" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">Philippines</collectingCountry>
. Remarks. We examined the 
<typeStatus box="[484,578,836,860]" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barrion, Barrion-Dupo &amp; Heong" authorityYear="2012" box="[611,756,836,860]" class="Arachnida" family="Lycosidae" genus="Hippasa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="20" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinsiloides">
<emphasis box="[611,756,836,860]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">H. sinsiloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as well as several specimens from other provinces in South 
<collectingCountry box="[1388,1451,836,860]" name="China" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">China</collectingCountry>
and Southeast Asia, confirming that the species is widely distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[899,966,871,895]" name="China" pageId="20" pageNumber="36">China</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
